<help communications pemote>

Does an action specified by the user.  This has no other affect
than what other players make of it, but is useful when trying to
express one's feelings.  This command is different from emote in
that it is a possessive emote.  See the example below. 

Syntax:  pemote [message]

Example:  pemote fists shake with palsy!!   	And your name is Grock,
	Shows everyone in your room:  Grock's fists shake with palsy!!
<color=red>
See Also:  socials, say, gecho, emote, describe, title
</color></help>
